    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Martes foina, more commonly known as stone martens or beech martens, are found across Europe, and Central Asia. They are weasel-like carnivores that are more generally found in deciduous forests or on rocky hillsides.</Note_Text>
